data.current_description:
Initiates the approval of a list of transfers that triggered an additional [review](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/transfers/latest/post/transfers#request-review). Adyen sends the outcome of the approval request through webhooks.

To use this endpoint:
- Your API credential must have the **TransferService Approve** [role](https://docs.adyen.com/platforms/manage-access/webservice-roles/?tab=transfers_3).
 - The account holder must have the required [capabilities](https://docs.adyen.com/platforms/verification-overview/capabilities).
 
Reach out to your Adyen contact to set up these permissions.
data.description_suggestion: Initiates the approval of a list of transfers that triggered an additional review. Requires the **TransferService Approve** role and account holder capabilities. The operation accepts a list of transfer identifiers and returns a response confirming the approval request has been submitted. Adyen sends the final outcome of the approval through webhooks. Note: This operation does not immediately complete the transfer approval; it queues the transfers for approval processing.
data.reasoning: The current description lacks clarity on what the operation returns and the asynchronous nature of the approval process. Added explicit information about the response confirmation, webhook notification mechanism, and the important side effect that approval is asynchronous. This helps AI agents understand the operation's behavior and expected outcomes.
